in korea lesson five investigates the idea of history as competing narratives students examine three representations of the vietnam war the war as depicted in american history textbooks the war as exhibited at the war remnants museum in ho chi minh city and the war as represented in an effort to build a monument to the us south vietnam alliance by the vietnamese american community in wichita kansas download pdf+ table of contents modified february 2012 pdf legacies_vietnam_toc pdf 125.1 kb stanford university all rights reserved 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints rss+ rss xml feeds
